    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start for the intro. I also want to make sure they understand why this is so important compared to just \"procedural\" due process. Could you add a section explaining why relying on just procedural due process isn't enough when it comes to protecting these fundamental rights?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process goes beyond the basic \"fair process\" that procedural due process offers. Procedural due process is like a safety net, ensuring fair play in legal proceedings, but it doesn't always protect our deeper rights. Substantive due process digs deeper, guarding our essential freedoms from being trampled by government actions. It's like having a personal bodyguard for your rights, making sure the government can't just sneak in and take away your fundamental liberties, like freedom of speech, privacy, or the right to marry whom you love. Without substantive due process, we'd be left with a hollow promise of fairness, where the government could still do a lot of harmful things without consequence. It's this robust protection that truly upholds the spirit of our Constitution and the rights that define us as individuals.",
      "source": "target",
